# Payment / PCI Compliance Integration Guide

## Overview

This guide covers the integration of the OmniSight Payment / PCI Compliance framework into your embedded payment terminal product.

## Supported Standards

| Standard | Version | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| PCI-DSS | v4.0 | Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard |
| PCI-PTS | v6.x | PIN Transaction Security |
| EMV | L1/L2/L3 | Chip card transaction standards |
| P2PE | v3.x | Point-to-Point Encryption |

## Prerequisites

- CORE-05 Skill pack framework installed
- CORE-15 Security stack configured (secure boot + TEE)
- CORE-09 Safety & compliance framework (optional, for combined certification)

## Quick Start

### 1. PCI-DSS Control Mapping

```python
from backend.payment_compliance import (
    list_pci_dss_requirements,
    validate_pci_dss_gate,
)

# List all 12 PCI-DSS requirements
requirements = list_pci_dss_requirements()
for req in requirements:
    print(f"{req.req_id}: {req.title}")
    print(f"  Artifacts: {req.artifacts}")
    print(f"  Tasks: {req.tasks}")

# Validate your DAG against PCI-DSS Level {{ level | default('1') }}
result = validate_pci_dss_gate(dag, "{{ level | default('L1') }}", your_artifacts)
if result.passed:
    print("PCI-DSS gate passed!")
else:
    print(f"Missing artifacts: {result.missing_artifacts}")
```

### 2. HSM Integration

```python
from backend.payment_compliance import (
    create_hsm_session,
    hsm_generate_key,
    hsm_encrypt,
    close_hsm_session,
)

# Connect to {{ hsm_vendor | default('Thales payShield 10K') }}
session = create_hsm_session("{{ hsm_vendor_id | default('thales') }}")

# Generate a Base Derivation Key
bdk = hsm_generate_key(session.session_id, "bdk", "AES-256")

# Encrypt cardholder data
encrypted = hsm_encrypt(session.session_id, card_data, bdk["key_id"])

# Clean up
close_hsm_session(session.session_id)
```

### 3. P2PE Key Injection

```python
from backend.payment_compliance import run_p2pe_key_injection

result = run_p2pe_key_injection(
    hsm_vendor="{{ hsm_vendor_id | default('thales') }}",
    device_id="terminal-001",
    injection_method="kif_ceremony",  # or "remote_key_injection"
)
print(f"KSN: {result.key_serial_number}")
print(f"Check value: {result.ipek_check_value}")
```

### 4. EMV Testing

```python
from backend.payment_compliance import run_emv_test_stub

# Run all L1 tests
l1_results = run_emv_test_stub("L1")

# Run specific L2 category
l2_cvm = run_emv_test_stub("L2", "cardholder_verification")

# Run L3 brand acceptance
l3_brand = run_emv_test_stub("L3", "brand_acceptance")
```

### 5. Certification Artifact Generation

```python
from backend.payment_compliance import generate_cert_artifacts

bundle = generate_cert_artifacts(
    standard="pci_dss",
    level="L1",
    existing_artifacts=["network_diagram", "encryption_inventory"],
)

# Review gap analysis
for gap in bundle.gap_analysis:
    print(f"Need to create: {gap['name']} ({gap['artifact_id']})")
```

